message.content:
A 'willow_tree' is a deciduous tree that belongs to the Salix genus.
It typically has long, narrow leaves that are green-grey in color.
The tree can grow up to 65 feet in height with a width of approximately 30 feet.
The branches of a 'willow_tree' are slender and tend to droop downward, giving the tree a weeping appearance.
The bark of the tree is usually greyish-brown and smooth to the touch.
'Willow_trees' are commonly found near streams, rivers, or other bodies of water as they thrive in moist environments.
The wood of the 'willow_tree' is flexible and was commonly used in the past to make baskets, furniture, and cricket bats.
